// Tuple primitive tests (BT-417)
// Tuples are an Erlang interop type — they exist primarily to handle
// results from Erlang/OTP functions that return {ok, Value} or {error, Reason}.
// For general-purpose collections, prefer List, Dictionary, or Array.

// ⚠️ NOTE: Beamtalk does not have tuple literal syntax.
// Tuples arrive from Erlang FFI calls and are handled via isOk/isError/unwrap.
// The Tuple new / Tuple new: constructors exist for testing purposes only.

// Placeholder to satisfy E2E test parser
1 + 1
// => 2

// ===========================================================================
// CREATION (BT-422)
// ===========================================================================

// Tuple new returns an empty tuple
Tuple new
// => _

(Tuple new) class
// => Tuple

// Tuple new: is not supported (no meaningful init-from-map)
Tuple new: #{#a => 1}
// => ERROR: instantiation_error

// ===========================================================================
// DISPLAY (BT-536)
// ===========================================================================

// Tuple printString shows tuple format
(Tuple new) printString
// => {}

// ===========================================================================
// SIZE
// ===========================================================================

// Empty tuple has size 0
(Tuple new) size
// => 0
